Description: Oval handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay fine light brown; worn slip. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 28a, 21 - illustrated herewith - or perhaps 185, 4; see British Museum 2011,5004.36.). Name Agemo.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0388)
